So a star graph is a graph having **one node [center node] which is connected to all other nodes directly** 

So why not try all nodes "as the center of star graph"
For each node,
  **star graph = node itself(center node)  + all it's direct neighbors**

  Thus for each node treat it is as center node and **find sum of k highest value neighbors**
  [Take care of negative values =>  exclude negative values as they would decrease overall sum]



