Simple solution will be to do the basice math, and simulate the digits from the back

# Approach
- We'll start with the ends of both strings, and in each iteration (till we've iterated all the strings), we'll fetch the last digit from the $$nums1$$, $$nums2$$ if not available we'll default to 0.

- Then we'll sum the digits and also add the carry from the last iteration,

- Then we'll push the sum modulo 10 to the answer string.

- Also dont forget to update the carry variable.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$

